<item>
            <title>[LU-5680] sanity-hsm uses /etc/motd (which is probably of size 0)</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5680</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In various tests sanity-hsm copies /etc/hosts, /etc/passwd, or /etc/modt for use as the test file. /etc/motd is likely of size 0 and may defeat the use of bandwidth control for timing. Uses of /etc/* should be replaced with a generated files of known suitable size. We should also add explicit tests using files of size 0.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="26768">LU-5680</key>
            <summary>sanity-hsm uses /etc/motd (which is probably of size 0)</summary>
